New York state accounted for 117 deaths, passing Washington state, the initial epicenter of the U.S. outbreak, in the number of fatalities.
As the virus has spread and testing has increased, the United States has grown to the third-most cases in the world.
Health officials warned more than 10% of the country's health workers were now infected with coronavirus.
Most locations simply broke up large gatherings and sent people home because one of the last things health officials wanted was putting people in confined spaces like jails.
